oth verify as well as build upon your findings. One of the exciting ways to pull for reproducibility is to make documents directly linked to data and computation! In Figure 3, we are showing outputs from a Jupyter Notebook directly part of the published scientific narrative.","key":"EhcCsxASnF"}],"key":"wdMkk6NNuo"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":0},"end":{"line":62,"column":0}},"children":[{"type":"image","url":"/myst-test/build/interactive-9b0c896d60204655652968b6a2b5a88f.gif","urlSource":"./images/interactive.gif","key":"it5VW3Rlcq"},{"type":"text","value":"\n","key":"slc8P2SjKt"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Figure 3","key":"qdMtORO29Y"}],"key":"bauRVhQnm9"},{"type":"text","value":": Embedding data, interactivity and computation into a MyST article.","key":"DTNvdfP2mv"}],"key":"tTjdIITa06"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":63,"column":0},"end":{"line":64,"column":0}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To drive all of these features, the contents of a MyST document needs to be well defined. This is critical for powering interactive hovers, linked citations, and compatibility with scientific publishing standards like the Journal Article Metadata Tag Suite (JATS). We have an emerging specification for MyST, ","key":"rUHLG2OhlE"},{"type":"link","url":"https://spec.myst.tools","children":[{"type":"inlineCode","value":"myst-spec","key":"FfVZ1W2ZYM"}],"urlSource":"https://spec.myst.tools","key":"bgdSIMmQWN"},{"type":"text","value":", that aims to capture this information and transform it between many different formats, like PDF, Word, JSON, and JATS XML (Figure 4). This specification is arrived at through a community-centric MyST Enhancement Proposal (","key":"MmNElMZdjp"},{"type":"link","url":"https://compass.executablebooks.org/en/latest/meps.html","children":[{"type":"text","value":"MEP","key":"OGihAU8QF3"}],"urlSource":"https://compass.executablebooks.org/en/latest/meps.html","key":"lAKLwCSsDf"},{"type":"text","value":") process.","key":"FHbvwao1lM"}],"key":"TwFlmqqoYo"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":0},"end":{"line":67,"column":0}},"children":[{"type":"image","url":"/myst-test/build/structured-data-505611deb4d3a8c241f66f8dc67a401e.gif","urlSource":"./images/structured-data.gif","key":"bMwBCgtTqU"},{"type":"text","value":"\n","key":"xC5ZnoeO0P"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Figure 4","key":"W5sfZyRd8A"}],"key":"klZmnPyS0Y"},{"type":"text","value":": The data behind MyST is ","key":"pqQ0g6eIZL"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"structured","key":"dReMlzlqr2"}],"key":"WLUZNkcppC"},{"type":"text","value":", which means we can transform it into many different document types and use it to power all sorts of exciting features!","key":"TKbKphSlMu"}],"key":"qZIcf0wejG"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":68,"column":0},"end":{"line":69,"column":0}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"One of the common forms of scientific communication today is through PDF documents. MyST has excellent support for creating PDF documents, using a data-driven templating library called ","key":"hY6ysAd1aw"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"jtex","key":"aBwpqwtslM"},{"type":"text","value":". The document in Figure 5 was created using MyST!","key":"vUhZrOnR2E"}],"key":"aZ9CxSFHvM"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":0},"end":{"line":72,"column":0}},"children":[{"type":"image","url":"/myst-test/build/pdf-two-column-f60c14e3c4fb5ca09e09d4a4855ee3f7.png","urlSource":"./images/pdf-two-column.png","key":"XX851yaVSi"},{"type":"text","value":"\n","key":"i62ZpAPZfh"},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Figure 5","key":"v8TPCZAQDM"}],"key":"ZdRm3jCohf"},{"type":"text","value":": A PDF rendering through MyST.","key":"aJYmlViiek"}],"key":"xhDU3kC6AU"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":0},"end":{"line":74,"column":0}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Conclusion","key":"Y400eVj8Nz"}],"identifier":"conclusion","label":"Conclusion","html_id":"conclusion","implicit":true,"key":"FJnFQWRSwN"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":0},"end":{"line":76,"column":0}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"There are many opportunities to improve open-science communication, to make it more interactive, accessible, more reproducible, and both produce and use structured data throughout the research-writing process. The ","key":"iU2CjtGTjj"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"mystjs","key":"QdwPeYq43x"},{"type":"text","value":" ecosystem of tools is designed with structured data at its core. We would love if you gave it a try -- learn to get started at ","key":"h97sioTUU3"},{"type":"link","url":"https://myst.tools","children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://myst.tools","key":"ZoeabyrikA"}],"urlSource":"https://myst.tools","key":"Yu3W3e7hxm"},{"type":"text","value":".","key":"bI5sOzwPLh"}],"key":"ewOA642yXz"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":77,"column":0},"end":{"line":78,"column":0}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"References","key":"QzbMCsvgpe"}],"identifier":"references","label":"References","html_id":"references","implicit":true,"key":"UCPVf6tzVY"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":0},"end":{"line":80,"column":0}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Bourne, Philip E., Clark, Timothy W., Dale, Robert, De Waard, Anita, Herman, Ivan, Hovy, Eduard H., Shotton, David. (2012)\"Improving The Future of Research Communications and e-Scholarship\". FORCE11. doi:10.4230/DAGMAN.1.1.41","key":"svWLfeMiVG"}],"key":"SOM2W4Jama"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":0},"end":{"line":82,"column":0}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Head, A., Lo, K., Kang, D., Fok, R., Skjonsberg, S., Weld, D. S., & Hearst, M. A. (2021, May). Augmenting Scientific Papers with Just-in-Time, Position-Sensitive Definitions of Terms and Symbols. Proceedings o